{"title_page": "Domantas Sabonis", "text_new": "{{pp-pc|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Lithuanian basketball player}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox basketball biography\n| name = Domantas Sabonis\n| image = Domantas Sabonis (32768447291).jpg\n| caption = Sabonis with the Thunder in February 2017\n| position = [[Center (basketball)|Center]] / [[Power forward (basketball)|Power forward]]\n| height_ft = 6\n| height_in = 11\n| weight_lb = 240\n| league = [[National Basketball Association|NBA]] \n| team = Indiana Pacers\n| number = 11\n| nationality = Lithuanian \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1996|5|3}}\n| birth_place = [[Portland, Oregon]]\n| college = [[Gonzaga Bulldogs men's basketball|Gonzaga]] (2014\u20132016)\n| draft_year = 2016\n| draft_round = 1\n| draft_pick = 11\n| draft_team = [[Orlando Magic]] \n| career_start = 2012\n| career_end = \n| years1 = 2012\u20132014\n| team1 = [[Baloncesto M\u00e1laga|Unicaja M\u00e1laga]]\n| years2 = 2012\u20132013\n| team2 = [[CB Axarqu\u00eda|Cl\u00ednicas Rinc\u00f3n]]\n| years3 = {{nbay|2016|full=y}}\n| team3 = [[Oklahoma City Thunder]]\n| years4 = {{nbay|2017|start}}\u2013present\n| team4 = [[Indiana Pacers]]\n| highlights = \n* [[List of NBA All-Stars|NBA All-Star]] ({{nasg|2020}})\n* Lithuanian Player of the Year (2018, 2019)\n* [[Associated Press|AP]] Honorable Mention [[NCAA Men's Basketball All-Americans|All-American]] ([[2016 NCAA Men's Basketball All-Americans|2016]])\n* Second-team [[Academic All-American]] ([[2016 NCAA Men's Basketball All-Americans|2016]])\n* First-team All-[[West Coast Conference|WCC]] (2016)\n* Second-team All-WCC (2015)\n* WCC All-Freshman Team (2015)\n| profile = domantas_sabonis\n| bbr = sabondo01\n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalSport|Men's basketball}}\n{{MedalCountry|{{bk|LTU}}}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[EuroBasket]]}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[EuroBasket 2015|2015 France]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[European Youth Olympic Festival]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2011 European Youth Summer Olympic Festival|2011 Turkey]]|[[Basketball at the 2011 European Youth Summer Olympic Festival|Team]]}}\n}}\n'''Domantas Sabonis''' (born May 3, 1996) is a Lithuanian-American<ref>{{cite news|last=Telander|first=Rick|title=NBA All-Star demographic makes a notable|date=February 18, 2020|newspaper=Chicago Sun-Times|url=https://chicago.suntimes.com/2020/2/18/21143414/nba-all-star-game-white-american-players|accessdate=April 23, 2020|quote=Sabonis, it should be noted, was born in Portland while his father, Arvydas Sabonis, was playing for the Trail Blazers. But Domantas has dual citizenship and considers Kaunas, Lithuania, home.}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Katz|first1=Fred|title=Domantas Sabonis to play in Rising Stars Challenge|url=http://www.normantranscript.com/sports/domantas-sabonis-to-play-in-rising-stars-challenge/article_7280cc1c-e35d-11e6-94f1-0b43d3a02a25.html|work=Norman Transcript|quote=Though he was born in Portland, Ore., Sabonis has dual citizenship and plays for the Lithuanian National Team in international competition}}</ref> professional [[basketball]] player for the [[Indiana Pacers]] of the [[National Basketball Association]] (NBA). He previously played in Spain for [[Baloncesto M\u00e1laga|Unicaja M\u00e1laga]]'s junior and senior teams before playing two seasons of college basketball for [[Gonzaga Bulldogs men's basketball|Gonzaga]]. He is the son of the [[Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame|Basketball Hall of Famer]] [[Arvydas Sabonis]], and was born in [[Portland, Oregon|Portland]], while his father was playing for the [[Portland Trail Blazers]].\n\n==Early life==\nDomantas was born on May 3, 1996, in [[Portland, Oregon]], [[United States]] when his father [[Arvydas Sabonis]] was playing for the [[Portland Trail Blazers]], however he considers [[Kaunas]], [[Lithuania]] as his hometown.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Misevi\u010dius |first1=Laurynas R. |title=Patrioti\u0161kumo pavyzdys: kaip JAV gim\u0119s D. Sabonis savo gimtuoju miestu pavert\u0117 Kaun\u0105 |url=https://www.delfi.lt/krepsinis/herojai/patriotiskumo-pavyzdys-kaip-jav-gimes-d-sabonis-savo-gimtuoju-miestu-paverte-kauna.d?id=70411676 |website=[[DELFI]] |accessdate=16 February 2020 |language=lt}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Domantas Sabonis - Men's Basketball |url=https://gozags.com/sports/mens-basketball/roster/domantas-sabonis/366 |website=Gonzaga University Athletics |accessdate=16 February 2020 |language=en}}</ref> He is the youngest son of Arvydas and has two older brothers: \u017dygis (born 1991), Tautvydas (born 1992) and younger sister Au\u0161rin\u0117 (born 1997).<ref name=\"urb\">{{cite web |last1=Urbonas |first1=Donatas |title=Nepriklausomyb\u0117s vaiko pavyzdys: D.Sabonio fenomenas prasid\u0117jo Saboni\u0173 namuose |url=https://www.15min.lt/24sek/naujiena/nba/nepriklausomybes-vaiko-pavyzdys-d-sabonio-fenomenas-prasidejo-saboniu-namuose-1130-1275680 |website=[[15min.lt]] |accessdate=16 February 2020 |language=lt}}</ref> When Arvydas was once asked if any of his sons will follow his footsteps in basketball \u2013 he distinguished Domantas due to his stubbornness and because he is [[left handed]].<ref name=\"urb\"/>\n\n==Early career==\nDespite being only a 16-year-old, on September 5, 2012, Sabonis debuted for [[Baloncesto M\u00e1laga|Unicaja M\u00e1laga]] against [[Cibona Zagreb]].<ref>[https://www.basketnews.lt/news-53417-sabonis-debiutavo-unicaja-komandoje.html Sabonis debiutavo \u201eUnicaja\u201c komandoje]</ref> He was later loaned to [[CB Axarqu\u00eda|Cl\u00ednicas Rinc\u00f3n]] for the 2012\u201313 season. He returned to M\u00e1laga for the 2013\u201314 season and debuted in the [[Liga ACB]] on October 13, 2013,<ref>[http://www.krepsinis.net/naujiena/unicaja-su-d-saboniu-ir-m-kuzminsku-pergale-pradejo-ispanijos-cempionata/234275 \u201eUnicaja\u201c su D.Saboniu ir M.Kuzminsku pergale prad\u0117jo Ispanijos \u010dempionat\u0105]</ref> becoming the youngest Unicaja player to debut in the ACB (17 years, 5 months and 10 days).<ref>[http://www.krepsinis.net/naujiena/d-sabonis-tapo-jauniausiu-ispanijos-cempionate-zaidusiu-unicaja-zaideju/234290 D.Sabonis tapo jauniausiu Ispanijos \u010dempionate \u017eaidusiu \u201eUnicaja\u201c \u017eaid\u0117ju]</ref> On October 18, Sabonis debuted in the [[EuroLeague]] against [[Olympiacos B.C.|Olympiacos Piraeus]]. In February 2014, he finished in the top 10 for the 2013 [[FIBA Europe Young Men's Player of the Year Award]] voting.<ref>[http://www.fibaeurope.com/coid_,qIYgqUhJ-Ue6pPZvVE7q1.articleMode_on.html SARIC IS 2013 YOUNG MEN'S POY]</ref> His best ACB game came on May 3, when he scored 13 points on 100% shooting.<ref>[https://www.basketnews.lt/news-73138-per-18aji-gimtadieni-sabonis-suzaide-geriausias-sezono-rungtynes.html Per 18\u2013\u0105j\u012f gimtadien\u012f Sabonis su\u017eaid\u0117 geriausias sezono rungtynes]</ref> On May 10, Sabonis helped Unicaja's junior team win the Spain Youth Basketball League silver medal. In the final game, he recorded 14 points and eight rebounds.<ref>[https://www.basketnews.lt/news-73315-sabonis-su-unicaja-ispanijos-jaunimo-pirmenybese-iskovojo-sidabro-medalius.html Sabonis su \u201eUnicaja\u201c Ispanijos jaunimo pirmenyb\u0117se i\u0161kovojo sidabro medalius]</ref> In January 2015, he finished in the top 5 for the 2014 FIBA Europe Young Men's Player of the Year Award voting.<ref>[http://www.fibaeurope.com/coid_VUv2HC68IKQHKl,DKDnXz1.articleMode_on.html SARIC IS 2014 YOUNG MEN'S POY]</ref> During his time with Unicaja, he never signed a professional contract with salary in order to remain eligible for the [[National Collegiate Athletic Association|NCAA]].<ref>[http://www.15min.lt/24sek/naujiena/archyvas/domantas-sabonis-prisijungs-prie-pagrindines-unicaja-komandos-872-359169 Domantas Sabonis prisijungs prie pagrindin\u0117s \u201eUnicaja\u201c komandos]</ref>\n\n==College career==\n{{quote box|width=23em|align=right|quote=I like a lot of things about his game. He is extremely aggressive, plays with a motor, is always going hard. Really high level rebounder, great passer, physical player, and runs and moves exceptionally well for a big guy.|source= \u2014[[Mark Few]], Gonzaga head coach.<ref name=\"signing\">{{cite web|title=Domas Sabonis making early impression at Gonzaga|url=http://legacy.krem.com/story/sports/gonzaga-bulldogs/2014/10/15/domas-sabonis-making-early-impression-at-gonzaga/17334413/|date=October 15, 2014}}</ref>}}\n\n{{College athlete recruit start|40=no|collapse=no|year=2014}}\n{{College athlete recruit entry\n| recruit = Domantas Sabonis\n| position = PF\n| hometown = [[Kaunas|Kaunas, Lithuania]]\n| highschool = Sunny View School / Unicaja Malaga\n| feet = 6\n| inches = 10\n| weight = 210\n| commitdate = April 17, 2014\n| scout stars = NR\n| rivals stars = 4\n| 247 stars = 5\n| espn stars = NR\n| espn grade = NR\n| grayshirt = \n}}\n{{College athlete recruit end\n| year = 2014\n| rivals ref title = 2014 Gonzaga Rivals Commits\n| scout ref title = 2014 Gonzaga Scout Commits\n| 247 ref title = 2014 Gonzaga 24/7 Sports Commits\n| espn ref title = 2014 Gonzaga ESPN Commits\n| rivals school = gonzaga\n| scout s = 130\n| 247 school = gonzaga\n| espn schoolid = 2250\n| scout overall = NR\n| rivals overall = NR\n| 247 overall = #26\n| espn overall = NR\n| accessdate = April 23, 2016\n| bball = yes\n}}\n\n===Freshman season===\nSabonis declined a Unicaja offer of a 3-year $630,000 contract in order to play in the [[National Collegiate Athletic Association|NCAA]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Domas Sabonis a mini me of Arvydas, could he end up in Portland?|url=http://www.csnnw.com/blazers/domas-sabonis-mini-me-arvydas-could-he-end-portland|accessdate=July 27, 2015}}</ref> He [[National Letter of Intent|committed]] to [[NCAA Division I]] squad [[Gonzaga Bulldogs men's basketball|Gonzaga University]] prior to the 2014\u201315 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gozags.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/041714aaa.html|title=Domas Sabonis Signs Men's Basketball Letter-Of-Intent |date=April 17, 2014}}</ref><ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hguzOVKX84E Interview of Domas Sabonis]</ref> On November 14, 2014, Sabonis solidly debuted by scoring 14 points, grabbing 8 rebounds, and dishing 2 assists, along with one steal and one block in 20 minutes.<ref>[http://www.basketnews.lt/news-78541-ncaa-starte-puikus-sabonio-pasirodymas-video.html NCAA starte \u2013 puikus Sabonio pasirodymas (video)]</ref> On February 3, 2015, after averaging 13 points and 11 rebounds per 26 minutes he was named [[West Coast Conference]] Player of the Week.<ref>{{cite web|title=Gonzaga's Domantas Sabonis Named WCC Men's Basketball Player of the Week|url=http://www.wccsports.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/020215aab.html|accessdate=March 3, 2015}}</ref> After a stellar regular season with Gonzaga, Sabonis was named to the All-WCC Second team, as well as to the WCC All-Freshman team.<ref name=\"2015 WCC Awards\">{{cite web|title=WCC Announces 2015 Men's Basketball All-Conference Team|url=http://www.wccsports.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/030315aab.html|accessdate=March 3, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150305200139/http://www.wccsports.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/030315aab.html|archive-date=March 5, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> On March 10, the Gonzaga Bulldogs defeated the [[2014\u201315 BYU Cougars men's basketball team|BYU Cougars]] 91\u201375 and won the [[West Coast Conference|WCC Tournament]] Title for the third straight time.<ref>[http://www.gozags.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=26400&ATCLID=209951769 MBB Grabs Third Straight WCC Tournament Title] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402120658/http://www.gozags.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=26400&ATCLID=209951769 |date=April 2, 2015}}</ref><ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RkIM3LFKCOE Highlights - Gonzaga vs BYU (WCC Championship 2015) - VIDEO]</ref> Sabonis was one of the best players in the game with 15 points and 6 rebounds.<ref>[http://www.basketnews.lt/news-83023-solidziai-rungtyniavusio-sabonio-komanda-triumfavo-vakaru-pakrantes-konferencijoje.html Solid\u017eiai rungtyniavusio Sabonio komanda triumfavo Vakar\u0173 pakrant\u0117s konferencijoje]</ref><ref>[http://www.krepsinis.net/naujiena/d-sabonis-svariai-prisidejo-prie-bulldogs-triumfo-vakaru-pakrantes-konferencijos-finale/248834 D.Sabonis svariai prisid\u0117jo prie \u201eBulldogs\u201c triumfo Vakar\u0173 pakrant\u0117s konferencijos finale]</ref> During [[2015 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament|March Madness]], Sabonis led Gonzaga to the Sweet 16 with 18 points and 9 rebounds.<ref>[http://www.gozags.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=26400&ATCLID=209977048 MBB Sweeps Past Iowa for Trip to Sweet 16] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402115730/http://www.gozags.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=26400&ATCLID=209977048 |date=April 2, 2015}}</ref> Gonzaga beat [[2014\u201315 UCLA Bruins men's basketball team|UCLA]] to make it to the Elite Eight, Gonzaga's first regional final with [[Mark Few]] as head coach and second overall. Sabonis scored 12 points and grabbed 8 rebounds during that game.<ref>[http://www.basketnews.lt/news-83645-bulldogs-su-saboniu-po-16-metu-pertraukos-pateko-tarp-8-geriausiu-ncaa-komandu-video.html \u201eBulldogs\u201c su Saboniu po 16 met\u0173 pertraukos pateko tarp 8 geriausi\u0173 NCAA komand\u0173 (video)]</ref> The season ended with a loss to the future champions [[2014\u201315 Duke Blue Devils men's basketball team|Duke]] and Sabonis was named to the NCAA Tournament South Regional All-Tournament team.<ref>{{cite web|title=Notebook: Zag seniors already missed|url=http://www.spokesman.com/zags/stories/2015/mar/29/notebook-zag-seniors-already-missed/|accessdate=March 29, 2015}}</ref> In his first NCAA season, Sabonis averaged 9.7 points, along with Gonzaga team highs of 66.8% field-goal percentage and 7.1 rebounds.<ref>[http://www.basketnews.lt/news-84146-ncaa-lietuviai-nuo-debiutavusio-sabonio-iki-prestizini-universiteta-baigiancio-malduno.html NCAA lietuviai: nuo debiutavusio Sabonio iki presti\u017ein\u012f universitet\u0105 baigian\u010dio Mald\u016bno]</ref>\n\nOn April 4, Few told [[ESPN]] that Sabonis planned to return for his sophomore season at Gonzaga, adding that Sabonis never seriously considered declaring for the [[2015 NBA draft]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Domantas Sabonis back to Gonzaga|url=http://espn.go.com/mens-college-basketball/story/_/id/12618334/domantas-sabonis-returning-gonzaga-bulldogs||accessdate=April 4, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Sophomore season===\nOn August 13, 2015, [[ESPN]] placed Sabonis 20th in its NCAA players rankings heading for the 2015\u201316 season, describing him as \"one of the nation's best, and edgiest, rebounders\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Updated top 25 players for 2015-2016|url=http://espn.go.com/mens-college-basketball/insider/story/_/id/13388093/updated-look-top-25-players-college-basketball-2015-2016-season|date=August 13, 2015}}</ref>\n{{quote box|width=23em|align=right|quote=No one plays harder than Gonzaga's Domantas Sabonis. The sophomore forward is a walking double-double, which could earn him third-team All-American honors.|source= \u2014Jeff Goodman, [[ESPN]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Upperclassmen dominate Goodman's midseason All-Americans|url=http://espn.go.com/mens-college-basketball/insider/story/_/id/14516523/michigan-state-spartans-denzel-valentine-makes-jump-midseason-all-american-team|date=January 7, 2016}}</ref>}}\n\nSabonis began his [[2015\u201316 Gonzaga Bulldogs men's basketball team|second NCAA season]] with an outstanding career-high performance of 26 points (2FG: 12/13, FT: 2/2); he also added 7 rebounds in a 91\u201352 win over Northern Arizona.<ref>{{cite web|title=No. 10 MBB Cruises to 91-52 Win Over N. Arizona|url=http://www.gozags.com/sports/m-baskbl/recaps/111815aaa.html|website=GoZags.com|accessdate=November 19, 2015}}</ref> On December 19, Sabonis set a new career high in points and rebounds, scoring 36 points (FG: 12/16, FT: 12/15) and adding a 16 rebounds; his team won 86\u201379.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sabonis Scores 36 As MBB Holds Off Tennessee 86-79|url=http://www.gozags.com/sports/m-baskbl/recaps/121915aaa.html|date=December 19, 2015}}</ref> The Zags' head coach [[Mark Few]] said that he never had seen a monster line like that for a Zag.<ref>{{cite web|title=Domantas Sabonis' big night leads Gonzaga past Tennessee in Seattle|url=http://www.spokesman.com/stories/2015/dec/19/domantas-sabonis-leads-gonzaga-past-tennessee-in-s/|accessdate=December 19, 2015}}</ref> Two days later, Sabonis improved on another career high by dishing out 6 assists; he also scored 23 points, grabbed 8 rebounds, and led Gonzaga past the [[Pepperdine Waves men's basketball|Pepperdine Waves]] 99-73.<ref>{{cite web|title=MBB Makes 16 Threes to Beat Pepperdine 99-73|url=http://www.gozags.com/sports/m-baskbl/recaps/122115aaa.html|date=December 21, 2015}}</ref> On January 2, 2016, he was just one point shy of his scoring record with 35 points; he also added 14 rebounds, 4 assists, and 3 blocks in a thrilling come-from-behind victory in [[Overtime (sports)#Basketball|OT]] versus the [[San Francisco Dons men's basketball|San Francisco Dons]] 102\u201394.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sabonis, Gonzaga Rally Late to Beat SF in OT, 102-94|url=http://www.gozags.com/sports/m-baskbl/recaps/010216aaa.html|date=January 2, 2016}}</ref> On January 9, Sabonis once again improved his rebounds record by grabbing 17 rebounds, and adding 28 points, 3 steals, 3 blocks and 4 assists, his team won 85\u201374. After the game, the Bulldogs head coach Mark Few said: \"Sabonis, none of us can take for granted the type of year he is having... Such consistency, it's amazing\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Wiltjer, Sabonis Lead MBB Over Portland 85-74|url=http://www.gozags.com/sports/m-baskbl/recaps/010916aaa.html|date=January 9, 2016}}</ref> On January 21, nearly posted a [[Double (basketball)#Triple-double|triple-double]] with 17 points, 13 rebounds, and a career-high 7 assists.<ref>{{cite web|title=Gonzaga Drops Road Contest at Saint Mary's, 70-67|url=http://www.gozags.com/sports/m-baskbl/recaps/012116aaa.html|date=January 21, 2016}}</ref> Two days later, Sabonis grabbed a new career high of 20 rebounds, as well as 12 points and 2 assists.<ref>{{cite web|title=Second-Half Surge Pushes Gonzaga past Pacific 71-61|url=http://www.gozags.com/sports/m-baskbl/recaps/012316aaa.html|date=January 23, 2016}}</ref> He was named to the 35-man midseason watchlist for the [[Naismith College Player of the Year|Naismith Trophy]] on February 11.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Payne|first1=Terrence|title=Naismith Trophy midseason list announced|url=http://www.foxsports.com/college-basketball/story/oklahoma-sooners-buddy-hield-lsu-tigers-ben-simmons-naismith-trophy-35-finalists-021116|accessdate=February 19, 2016|work=[[Fox Sports]]|date=February 11, 2016}}</ref> On March 1, he was included into the First-team All-[[West Coast Conference|WCC]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Domantas Sabonis nominuotas \u012f pirm\u0105j\u0105 konferencijos komand\u0105|url=http://www.basketnews.lt/news-95275-domantas-sabonis-nominuotas-i-pirmaja-konferencijos-komanda.html|website=BasketNews.lt|accessdate=March 1, 2016}}</ref> Two days later, Sabonis received [[Academic All-America|CoSIDA Academic All-American]] honors.<ref>{{cite web|title=MBB's Sabonis Named CoSIDA Academic All-American|url=http://www.gozags.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/030316aac.html|website=GoZags.com|accessdate=March 6, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn March 17, Sabonis began his second [[2016 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament|March Madness]] appearance by leading his team past the [[2015\u201316 Seton Hall Pirates men's basketball team|Seton Hall Pirates]] 68-52 to the Round of 32, scoring 21 points, grabbing 16 rebounds and making 4 assists, despite having a flu.<ref>{{cite web|title=Gonzaga Upsets Seton Hall in Round of 64, 68-52|url=http://www.gozags.com/sports/m-baskbl/recaps/031716aaa.html|website=GoZags.com|accessdate=March 17, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Gonzaga vs. Seton Hall - Box Score|url=http://espn.go.com/ncb/boxscore?gameId=400871287|website=ESPN.go.com|accessdate=March 17, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Neeilin\u0117 D.Sabonio naktis: \u0161ou nesustabd\u0119s gripas ir var\u017eovui i\u0161narintas petys|url=http://www.15min.lt/24sek/naujiena/amerika/neeiline-d-sabonio-naktis-sou-nesustabdes-gripas-ir-varzovui-isnarintas-petys-873-597801|website=24sek.lt|accessdate=March 18, 2016}}</ref> On March 19, he helped his team to advance into the Sweet 16 stage with 19 points, 10 rebounds, 3 assists and 2 steals, crushing the third-seeded [[2015\u201316 Utah Utes men's basketball team|Utah Utes]] 82\u201359.<ref>{{cite web|title=MBB Routs Utah 82-59 to move to Sweet 16|url=http://www.gozags.com/sports/m-baskbl/recaps/031916aac.html|website=GoZags.com|accessdate=March 19, 2016}}</ref> Moreover, he limited his direct opponent and one of the top prospects [[Jakob P\u00f6ltl]] to just 5 points and 4 rebounds.<ref>{{cite web|title=No. 11 Gonzaga throttles Utah|url=https://www.ncaa.com/game/basketball-men/d1/2016/03/19/gonzaga-utah|website=NCAA.com|accessdate=March 19, 2016}}</ref> Following it, Sabonis was the most efficient post-up player left in the NCAA tournament.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Winn|first1=Luke|title=Gonzaga forward Domantas Sabonis is the best big man left in the NCAAs|url=http://www.campusrush.com/gonzaga-bulldogs-basketball-domantas-sabonis-ncaa-tournament-1676850010.html?xid=si_social|website=CampRush.com|accessdate=March 21, 2016}}</ref> Despite his yet another monster performance of 19 points, 17 rebounds (7 offensive) and 5 blocks on March 25, his journey was stopped by the [[2015\u201316 Syracuse Orange men's basketball team|Syracuse Orange]] during the final match moments, losing 60\u201363.<ref>{{cite web|title=SU beats Gonzaga in final moments|url=https://www.ncaa.com/game/basketball-men/d1/2016/03/25/gonzaga-syracuse/|website=NCAA.com|accessdate=March 25, 2016}}</ref> In his second NCAA season Sabonis almost doubled his every single statistical line comparing with the previous season.<ref>{{cite web|title=Domas Sabonis|url=http://basketball.realgm.com/player/Domas-Sabonis/Summary/33381|website=Basketball.RealGM.com|accessdate=March 26, 2016}}</ref> During the March Madness, his averages were 19.6 points, 14.3 rebounds, 2.6 assists and 3.3 blocks.<ref>{{cite web|title=ESPN su\u017eav\u0117j\u0119s Domantas Sabonis sulauk\u0117 puikios NBA naujok\u0173 bir\u017eos prognoz\u0117s|url=http://www.15min.lt/24sek/naujiena/amerika/espn-suzavejes-domantas-sabonis-sulauke-puikios-nba-naujoku-birzos-prognozes-873-602179|website=24sek.lt|accessdate=March 28, 2016}}</ref> On March 29, Sabonis was named to the [[CBS]] College Basketball All-America Third-team, along with [[Ben Simmons]], [[Brandon Ingram]], [[Jamal Murray]] and [[Yogi Ferrell]].<ref>{{cite web|title=CBS Sports 2015-16 College Basketball All-America Team, Coach of the Year|url=http://www.cbssports.com/collegebasketball/eye-on-college-basketball/25534690/cbs-sports-2015-16-college-basketball-all-america-team-coach-of-the-year|website=CBSSPORTS.com|accessdate=March 29, 2016}}</ref> Sabonis also was one of the finalists in [[Kareem Abdul-Jabbar Award]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Goon |first1=Kyle |title=Utah basketball: Jakob Poeltl wins Kareem Abdul-Jabbar Award for top center |url=https://archive.sltrib.com/article.php?id=3756599&itype=CMSID |website=sltrib.com |date=8 April 2016 |accessdate=21 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Professional career==\n\n===NBA draft preparation===\nIn early April 2016, several U.S. media reports indicated that he would declare himself eligible for the [[2016 NBA draft]] and would hire an [[Sports agent|agent]], marking the end of his career at Gonzaga.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbssports.com/collegebasketball/eye-on-college-basketball/25545148/gonzagas-domantas-sabonis-son-of-hall-of-famer-is-ready-for-nba-draft |title=Gonzaga's Domantas Sabonis, son of Hall of Famer, is ready for NBA Draft |first=Sam |last=Vecenie |work=[[CBSSports.com]] |date=April 8, 2016|accessdate=April 14, 2016}}</ref> On April 20, he signed with Jason Ranne and Greg Lawrence of [[Wasserman Media Group]] for representation in the NBA draft.<ref>{{cite web|title=D. Sabonis ver\u017eiasi \u012f NBA: pasisamd\u0117 du agentus ir \u012f NCAA nebegr\u012f\u0161|url=http://www.delfi.lt/krepsinis/naujienos/d-sabonis-verziasi-i-nba-pasisamde-du-agentus-ir-i-ncaa-nebegris.d?id=71037236|website=Krepsinis.lt|language=lt-LT|accessdate=April 20, 2016}}</ref> Prior to the draft, he rejected the offer to participate in [[NBA Draft Combine]].<ref>{{cite web|title=D. Sabonis atsisak\u0117 kvietimo \u012f presti\u017ein\u0119 NBA stovykl\u0105|url=http://www.delfi.lt/krepsinis/naujienos/d-sabonis-atsisake-kvietimo-i-prestizine-nba-stovykla.d?id=71196212|website=Krepsinis.lt|language=lt-LT|accessdate=June 6, 2016}}</ref> Instead, he participated in four pre-draft workouts with the [[Phoenix Suns]], [[Toronto Raptors]], [[Boston Celtics]] and [[Utah Jazz]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Domanto Sabonio labiausiai nori keturios NBA komandos|url=https://www.basketnews.lt/news-98658-domanto-sabonio-labiausiai-nori-keturios-nba-komandos.html|website=BasketNews.lt|language=lt-LT|accessdate=June 9, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Oklahoma City Thunder (2016\u20132017)===\nSabonis was selected 11th overall by the [[Orlando Magic]] in the [[2016 NBA draft]].<ref>{{cite web|title=NBA duris prav\u0117r\u0117 antras Sabonis: Domantui \u2013 11-as \u0161aukimas!|url=http://www.delfi.lt/krepsinis/naujienos/nba-duris-pravere-antras-sabonis-domantui-11-as-saukimas.d?id=71646656|website=Krepsinis.lt|language=lt-LT|accessdate=June 24, 2016}}</ref> He was traded to the [[Oklahoma City Thunder]] along with [[Ersan \u0130lyasova]] and [[Victor Oladipo]] for [[Serge Ibaka]] on draft night.<ref>{{cite web|title=Domantas Sabonis i\u0161keistas \u012f \"Thunder\"|url=https://www.basketnews.lt/news-99017-domantas-sabonis-iskeistas-i-thunder.html|website=BasketNews.lt|language=lt-LT|date=June 24, 2016|accessdate=June 24, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Domantas Sabonis traded to Oklahoma City Thunder in deal sending Serge Ibaka to Orlando: report|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/nba/index.ssf/2016/06/domantas_sabonis_in_the_2016_n.html|publisher=Oregon Live|date=June 23, 2016|accessdate=June 24, 2016}}</ref> He did not participate in the [[2016 NBA Summer League]] in order to join the [[Lithuania men's national basketball team]] training camp.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Slater|first1=Anthony|title=OKC Thunder: Domantas Sabonis expected to compete for Lithuania in the Olympics, miss summer league|url=http://newsok.com/article/5506585|website=NEWSOK.com|accessdate=June 26, 2016}}</ref> On August 12, 2016, he signed his rookie scale contract with the Thunder.<ref>{{cite web|title=Thunder Signs Domantas Sabonis|url=http://www.nba.com/thunder/news/sabonis-signing-160812|work=NBA.com|date=August 12, 2016|accessdate=August 12, 2016}}</ref> He made his debut for the Thunder in their season opener as their starting power forward on October 26, recording five points and four rebounds in 16 minutes as a starter in a 103\u201397 win over the [[Philadelphia 76ers]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/boxscore?gameId=400899389|title=Thunder vs. 76ers \u2013 Box Score|work=ESPN.com|date=October 26, 2016|accessdate=October 27, 2016}}</ref> He became the first Thunder player to debut as a starting five member since [[Kevin Durant]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.delfi.lt/krepsinis/herojai/is-tevo-seselio-islisti-bandantis-d-sabonis-nba-kuria-savaja-istorija.d?id=72823248|title=I\u0161 t\u0117vo \u0161e\u0161\u0117lio i\u0161l\u012fsti bandantis D. Sabonis NBA kuria sav\u0105j\u0105 istorij\u0105|work=delfi.lt|date=November 10, 2016|accessdate=November 10, 2016|language=lt-LT}}</ref> On November 7, he recorded season highs of 15 points and 10 rebounds in a 97\u201385 win over the [[Miami Heat]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/recap?gameId=400899547|title=Kanter scores 24 as Thunder beat Heat 97-85|work=ESPN.com|date=November 7, 2016|accessdate=November 8, 2016}}</ref> On December 23, he set a new season high with 20 points on 8-of-11 shooting in a 117\u2013112 win over the [[Boston Celtics]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/recap?gameId=400899887|title=Westbrook triple-double leads Thunder past Celtics 117-112|work=ESPN.com|date=December 23, 2016|accessdate=December 23, 2016}}</ref> On January 25, 2017, he was named in the World Team for the 2017 [[Rising Stars Challenge]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/article/2017/01/25/2017-rising-stars-challenge-participants-official-release|title=Minnesota's Towns and Philadelphia's Embiid headline roster for 2017 BBVA Compass Rising Stars Challenge|work=NBA.com|date=January 25, 2017|accessdate=February 1, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Richardson|first=Tamberlyn|url=http://thunderousintentions.com/2017/01/25/domantas-sabonis-bbva-rising-stars/|title=Domantas Sabonis Named to BBVA Rising Stars Game at All-Star Weekend|work=ThunderousIntentions.com|date=January 25, 2017|accessdate=January 26, 2017}}</ref> Six days later, he matched his season high with 13 rebounds and had 13 points in a 108\u201394 loss to the [[San Antonio Spurs]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/recap?gameId=400900148|title=Leonard's 36 points lead Spurs by Thunder, Westbrook, 108-94|work=ESPN.com|date=January 31, 2017|accessdate=February 1, 2017}}</ref> On February 18, he scored 10 points on 5-of-8 shooting in only 12 minutes to help Team World defeat Team USA 150\u2013141 in the [[Rising Stars Challenge]] during [[2017 NBA All-Star Game|All-Star Weekend]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Seiler|first=Anthony|url=http://thunderousintentions.com/2017/02/18/okc-thunder-rooks-part-world-win/|title=OKC Thunder Rookies Sabonis and Abrines Display Talent In Rising Stars Game|work=ESPN.com|date=February 18, 2017|accessdate=April 12, 2017}}</ref> Sabonis transitioned to a bench role in early March, following the acquisition of [[Taj Gibson]] at the trade deadline.<ref>{{cite web|last=Horne|first=Erik|url=http://newsok.com/article/5541083|title=Thunder starts Taj Gibson over Domantas Sabonis against Spurs|work=NewsOK.com|date=March 9, 2017|accessdate=April 12, 2017}}</ref> In his debut season, he was a member of the starting five in 66 of 81 games.<ref>{{cite web|title=Domantas Sabonis|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/player/stats/_/id/3155942/domantas-sabonis|website=ESPN.com|accessdate=April 19, 2017}}</ref> The Thunder qualified for the [[2017 NBA Playoffs|NBA Playoffs]] as the sixth seed, but they were eliminated 4\u20131 by the [[Houston Rockets]] in the first round; Sabonis played just six minutes in the series, as he managed court time in just two of the five games.<ref>{{cite web|title=Po debiutinio D.Sabonio pasirodymo NBA \u2013 ai\u0161kios gair\u0117s tobul\u0117jimui ir prognoz\u0117 kitam sezonui|url=http://www.krepsinis.net/naujiena/po-debiutinio-d-sabonio-pasirodymo-nba-aiskios-gaires-tobulejimui-ir-prognoze-kitam-sezonui/273257|website=Krepsinis.net|accessdate=April 26, 2017|language=lt-LT}}</ref> Upon concluding his rookie season, Sabonis indicated that he would participate in the [[2017 NBA Summer League]] in preparation for [[EuroBasket 2017]].<ref>{{cite web|title=D. Sabonis jau susiplanavo atostogas: dalyvaus vestuv\u0117se ir \u017eais NBA vasaros lygoje|url=http://www.delfi.lt/nba/naujienos/d-sabonis-jau-susiplanavo-atostogas-dalyvaus-vestuvese-ir-zais-nba-vasaros-lygoje.d?id=74479064|website=DELFI.lt|accessdate=April 27, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Indiana Pacers (2017\u2013present)===\n{{quote box|width=24em|align=right|quote=Players respect me now, players depend on me\", \"My teammates, when the game is tough they tell me, 'C'mon Domas, we need you,' and I like that, I like taking that responsibility.|source=\u2014Domantas Sabonis, about his third season in the NBA.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Uggetti |first1=Paolo |title=Domantas Sabonis Can't Miss |url=https://www.theringer.com/nba/2018/12/19/18147846/domantas-sabonis-indiana-pacers |website=The Ringer |accessdate=December 25, 2018 |date=December 19, 2018}}</ref>}}\n\nOn July 6, 2017, Sabonis was traded, along with [[Victor Oladipo]], to the [[Indiana Pacers]] in exchange for [[Paul George]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/pacers/news/pacers-acquire-oladipo-and-sabonis|title=Pacers Acquire Oladipo and Sabonis|work=NBA.com|date=July 6, 2017|accessdate=July 6, 2017}}</ref> Due to the unexpected trade, he not only missed the [[2017 NBA Summer League]], but was also ruled out from representing the Lithuanian national team during [[EuroBasket 2017]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Nuog\u0105stavimai virto realybe: D. Sabonis priverstas praleisti Europos \u010dempionat\u0105|url=http://www.delfi.lt/krepsinis/eurobasket/nuogastavimai-virto-realybe-d-sabonis-priverstas-praleisti-europos-cempionata.d?id=75271809|website=Krepsinis.lt|accessdate=July 20, 2017}}</ref> In his debut for the Pacers in their season opener on October 18, Sabonis had 16 points and seven rebounds in a 140\u2013131 win over the [[Brooklyn Nets]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/recap?gameId=400974701|title=Revamped Pacers rely on new faces to cut down Nets 140-131|work=ESPN.com|date=October 18, 2017|accessdate=October 18, 2017}}</ref> On October 29, he had 22 points and 12 rebounds, both career highs, while going 9 of 9 from the field in a 97\u201394 win over the [[San Antonio Spurs]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/recap?gameId=400974837|title=Oladipo's late 3 gives Pacers rare 97-94 win over Spurs|work=ESPN.com|date=October 29, 2017|accessdate=October 29, 2017}}</ref> Two days later, he recorded a career-high 16 rebounds in addition to 12 points and five assists in a 101\u201383 win over the [[Sacramento Kings]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/recap?gameId=400974852|title=Bogdanovic leads Pacers to 101-83 rout of Kings|work=ESPN.com|date=October 31, 2017|accessdate=October 31, 2017}}</ref> On November 2, he recorded a career-high six assists in addition to 15 points and 12 rebounds in a 124\u2013107 win over the [[Cleveland Cavaliers]].<ref>{{cite web|title=D. Sabonis v\u0117l gerino karjeros rekordus \u2013 \"Pacers\" sutriu\u0161kino L. Jameso kariaun\u0105|url=https://www.delfi.lt/nba/naujienos/d-sabonis-vel-gerino-karjeros-rekordus-pacers-sutriuskino-l-jameso-kariauna.d?id=76226741|website=DELFI.lt|accessdate=November 2, 2017}}</ref> On December 18, he had a career-high three blocked shots to go with 17 points and eight rebounds in a 109\u201397 win over the Nets.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sabonio naktis Brukline \u2013 rezultatyvus \u017eaidimas, asmeninis blok\u0173 rekordas ir \"Pacers\" pergal\u0117|url=https://www.delfi.lt/nba/naujienos/sabonio-naktis-brukline-rezultatyvus-zaidimas-asmeninis-bloku-rekordas-ir-pacers-pergale.d?id=76669499|website=Krepsinis.lt|accessdate=December 18, 2017}}</ref> On January 3, 2018, he had a career-high 24 points on 10-of-13 shooting in a 122\u2013101 loss to the [[Milwaukee Bucks]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/recap?gameId=400975307|title=Giannis gets double-double in Bucks' 122-101 win over Pacers|work=ESPN.com|date=January 3, 2018|accessdate=January 3, 2018}}</ref> While participating in the [[Rising Stars Challenge#2018 game|2018 NBA Rising Stars Challenge]], Sabonis recorded 13 points, 11 rebounds and three assists to help Team World defeat Team USA 155\u2013124.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kylan\u010di\u0173 \u017evaig\u017ed\u017ei\u0173 rungtyn\u0117se be klaid\u0173 atakav\u0119s Sabonis pasi\u017eym\u0117jo gra\u017eiu dvigubu dubliu|url=https://www.delfi.lt/nba/naujienos/kylanciu-zvaigzdziu-rungtynese-be-klaidu-atakaves-sabonis-pasizymejo-graziu-dvigubu-dubliu.d?id=77194035|website=DELFI|accessdate=February 17, 2018}}</ref> On April 8, he scored a career-high 30 points in a 123\u2013117 win over the [[Charlotte Hornets]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/recap?gameId=400975943|title=Sabonis scores career-high 30, Pacers beat Hornets 123-117|work=ESPN.com|date=April 8, 2018|accessdate=April 8, 2018}}</ref> In Game 5 of the Pacers' first-round [[2018 NBA Playoffs|playoff]] series against the Cavaliers, Sabonis scored a playoff career-high 22 points in a 98\u201395 loss.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nuostab\u0173 Sabonio pasirodym\u0105 u\u017etemd\u0117 LeBrono trita\u0161kis su sirena ir grubi arbitro klaida|url=https://www.basketnews.lt/news-120159-nuostabu-sabonio-pasirodyma-uztemde-lebrono-tritaskis-su-sirena-ir-grubi-arbitro-klaida.html|website=BasketNews.lt|accessdate=April 26, 2018|language=lt-LT}}</ref>\n\nOn September 26, 2018, the Pacers picked up the team option on Sabonis' contract.<ref>{{cite web |title=Pacers Pick Up Contract Options on Leaf, Sabonis |url=https://www.nba.com/pacers/news/pacers-pick-contract-options-leaf-sabonis |website=NBA.com |accessdate=September 27, 2018 |date=September 26, 2018}}</ref> On October 31, he was 12-for-12 shooting while matching his career high with 30 points in a 107\u2013101 win over the [[New York Knicks]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/recap?gameId=401070786|title=Sabonis, Oladipo lift Pacers over Knicks 107-101|work=ESPN.com|date=October 31, 2018|accessdate=October 31, 2018}}</ref> On November 19, he had 19 points, nine rebounds and a career-high nine assists in a 121\u201394 win over the [[Utah Jazz]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/recap?gameId=401070922|title=Pacers hit all right notes in 121-94 blowout over Jazz|work=ESPN.com|date=November 19, 2018|accessdate=November 19, 2018}}</ref> In December 2018, he was chosen as the Lithuanian Player of the Year by the [[Lithuanian Basketball Federation]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rimkus |first1=K\u0119stas |title=Domantas Sabonis nurung\u0117 Jon\u0105 Valan\u010di\u016bn\u0105 geriausio \u0161alies krep\u0161ininko rinkimuose |url=https://www.15min.lt/24sek/naujiena/lietuva/domantas-sabonis-nurunge-jona-valanciuna-geriausio-salies-krepsininko-rinkimuose-875-1068574 |website=15min.lt/24sek |accessdate=December 4, 2018}}</ref> On March 19, 2019, he tied a career high with 16 rebounds in a 115\u2013109 loss to the [[Los Angeles Clippers]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/recap?gameId=401071737|title=Clippers edge Pacers 115-109 at home for 1st time since 2014|work=ESPN.com|date=March 19, 2019|accessdate=March 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn October 21, 2019, one day before start of the [[2019\u201320 NBA season|2019\u201320 season]], Sabonis signed a reported four-year contract extension with the Pacers.<ref>{{cite web |title=Pacers Sign Domantas Sabonis to Contract Extension |url=https://www.nba.com/pacers/news/pacers-sign-domantas-sabonis-contract-extension |website=NBA.com |accessdate=December 21, 2019 |date=October 21, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Sabonis agrees to 4-year, $77M deal with Pacers |url=https://www.espn.com/nba/story/_/id/27897423/domantas-sabonis-agrees-4-year-77-million-deal-pacers |website=ESPN.com |accessdate=November 2, 2019 |date=October 21, 2019}}</ref> On November 1, Sabonis recorded a new career high with 17 rebounds in a 102\u201395 win versus the [[Cleveland Cavaliers]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Atkovot\u0173 kamuoli\u0173 rekord\u0105 pagerin\u0119s Sabonis ved\u0117 \"Pacers\" \u012f antr\u0105 pergal\u0119 |url=https://www.delfi.lt/krepsinis/nba/atkovotu-kamuoliu-rekorda-pagerines-sabonis-vede-pacers-i-antra-pergale.d?id=82682317 |website=[[DELFI]] |accessdate=November 2, 2019 |language=lt-LT}}</ref> On November 18, Sabonis yet again improved his career rebounds record by grabbing 18 rebounds, and helping his team to get a 115\u201386 victory versus the [[Brooklyn Nets]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Galingai \u017eaidusio Sabonio s\u0105skaitoje \u2013 naujas rekordas, \"Pacers\" \u2013 triu\u0161kinama pergal\u0117 |url=https://www.delfi.lt/krepsinis/nba/galingai-zaidusio-sabonio-saskaitoje-naujas-rekordas-pacers-triuskinama-pergale.d?id=82820797 |website=[[DELFI]] |accessdate=November 19, 2019}}</ref> In December 2019, he was chosen as the Lithuanian Player of the Year for a second consecutive year.<ref>{{cite web |title=Paskelbti geriausi Lietuvos met\u0173 krep\u0161ininkai \u2013 Sabas d\u0117kojo s\u016bnaus vardu |url=https://www.delfi.lt/krepsinis/naujienos/paskelbti-geriausi-lietuvos-metu-krepsininkai-sabas-dekojo-sunaus-vardu.d?id=82951947 |website=[[DELFI]] / [[ELTA]] |accessdate=December 3, 2019}}</ref> On December 15, 2019, Sabonis got his 12th consecutive [[Double-double (basketball)|double-double]] and improved previous Pacers record for the most consecutive double-doubles, which was held by [[Troy Murphy]] since 2009.<ref>{{cite web |title=Pergalingose \"Pacers\" rungtyn\u0117se Domantas Sabonis tapo klubo rekordininku |url=https://www.basketnews.lt/news-135628-pergalingose-pacers-rungtynese-domantas-sabonis-tapo-klubo-rekordininku.html |website=BasketNews.lt |accessdate=16 December 2019 |language=lt-LT}}</ref> On January 21, 2020, Sabonis became the first Lithuanian in the NBA history to record a [[Double-double (basketball)#Triple-double|triple-double]] with 22 points, 15 rebounds and 10 assists as the Pacers won 115\u2013107 over the [[Denver Nuggets]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Istorinis pasiekimas: pergal\u0117s fone Sabonis pirmas i\u0161 lietuvi\u0173 NBA surinko trigub\u0105 dubl\u012f |url=https://www.delfi.lt/krepsinis/nba/istorinis-pasiekimas-pergales-fone-sabonis-pirmas-is-lietuviu-nba-surinko-triguba-dubli.d?id=83313929 |website=[[DELFI]] |accessdate=January 21, 2020}}</ref> On January 26, he recorded his second triple-double with 27 points, 14 rebounds and a career-high 11 assists.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sabonio trigubas dublis nei\u0161gelb\u0117jo \"Pacers\" ekipos m\u016b\u0161yje su \"Blazers\" |url=https://www.delfi.lt/krepsinis/naujienos/sabonio-trigubas-dublis-neisgelbejo-pacers-ekipos-musyje-su-blazers.d?id=83373109 |website=[[DELFI]] |accessdate=January 27, 2020}}</ref> On January 30, Sabonis was chosen to the [[2020 NBA All-Star Game]] after averaging 18 points, 12.8 rebounds, 4.6 assists, and became only the second Lithuanian to be chosen as an [[NBA All-Star]], the other being [[\u017dydr\u016bnas Ilgauskas]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Smith |first1=Sekou |title=Jimmy Butler, Chris Paul, Russell Westbrook highlight reserves for All-Star Game 2020 |url=https://www.nba.com/article/2020/01/30/2020-all-star-reserves-announced |website=NBA.com |accessdate=January 31, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Istorinis \u012fvertinimas: Sabonis pakviestas \u017eaisti \"Vis\u0173 \u017evaig\u017ed\u017ei\u0173\" rungtyn\u0117se |url=https://www.delfi.lt/krepsinis/nba/istorinis-ivertinimas-sabonis-pakviestas-zaisti-visu-zvaigzdziu-rungtynese.d?id=83415305 |website=[[DELFI]] |accessdate=January 31, 2020}}</ref> Sabonis also participated in the [[NBA All-Star Weekend Skills Challenge]] in 2020 and was just 1 shot away from the trophy, after being defeated only in the final by [[Bam Adebayo]].<ref>{{cite web |title=NBA All-Star 2020 event tracker: Participants named for 3-Point Contest, Dunk Contest, Skills Challenge |url=https://www.cbssports.com/nba/news/nba-all-star-2020-event-tracker-participants-named-for-3-point-contest-dunk-contest-skills-challenge/ |website=[[CBSSports.com]] |accessdate=6 February 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u012eg\u016bd\u017eiais NBA lyg\u0105 nustebin\u0119s Sabonis: parod\u0117me, kaip kei\u010diasi krep\u0161inis |url=https://www.delfi.lt/krepsinis/nba/igudziais-nba-lyga-nustebines-sabonis-parodeme-kaip-keiciasi-krepsinis.d?id=83547321 |website=[[DELFI]] |accessdate=16 February 2020 |language=lt}}</ref> During his first NBA All-Star Game appearance, Sabonis scored 2 points, grabbed 6 rebounds per 19 minutes and helped Team LeBron to win 157\u2013155.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Urbonas |first1=Donatas |title=NBA \u201eAll-Star\u201c ma\u010de \u2013 D.Sabonio krik\u0161tas, ne\u012ftik\u0117tina intriga ir Kobe \u0161iurpuliukai |url=https://www.15min.lt/24sek/naujiena/nba/nba-all-star-mace-d-sabonio-krikstas-neitiketina-intriga-ir-kobe-siurpuliukai-1130-1276914 |website=[[15min.lt]] |accessdate=17 February 2020 |language=lt}}</ref>\nSabonis particpated in the NBA 2K Players Tournament during the coronavirus pandemic, playing against [[Montrezl Harrell]], a center for the [[Los Angeles Clippers]] in an [[NBA 2K20]] basketball game as their respective basketball teams.<ref> https://www.sportingnews.com/us/nba/news/domantas-sabonis-gets-heated-at-his-virtual-self-in-nba-2k-players-tournament/huk0cxj564ep1jifun77vf3i3</ref>\n\n==National team career==\n[[File:Domantas Sabonis (2016 Summer Olympics).jpg|thumb|150px|right|Sabonis with the [[Lithuania men's national basketball team|Lithuanian national team]] during the 2016 Olympics.]]\n\n{{quote box|width=21em|align=left|quote=I can say that another basketball star is growing. His father was uncommon and such human is one per 100 years. I was thinking that if Domantas will not interfere the national team it will be good, but when he actually helps I appreciate it very nicely.|source= \u2014[[Jonas Kazlauskas]], describing [[Arvydas Sabonis]]'s son Domantas in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kazlauskas: apie rus\u0173 nor\u0105 nutraukti darb\u0105 rinktin\u0117je ir augan\u010di\u0105 Sabonio \u017evaig\u017ed\u0119|url=http://www.basketnews.lt/news-88412-kazlauskas-apie-rusu-nora-nutraukti-darba-rinktineje-ir-augancia-sabonio-zvaigzde.html|website=BasketNews.lt|accessdate=September 2, 2015 |language=lt}}</ref>}}\n\nSabonis made his international debut with the [[Lithuania men's national under-16 and under-17 basketball team|Lithuania U-16 national team]] at the [[2012 FIBA Europe Under-16 Championship|2012 FIBA U-16 European Championship]], averaging 14.1 points, 14.4 rebounds and 2.4 assists per game. He grabbed a tournament-high 27 rebounds against Poland on July 27. In 2013, at 17 years of age, Domantas played for Lithuania U-18 team in [[2013 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship]]. He averaged 14 points, 11.4 rebounds and 1.4 assists per game<ref>[http://u18men.fibaeurope.com/en/cid_2bqXUaQOJwYn9c2ymJyFx0.playerID_84314.compID_8aYeHlfuGF-mF5IqO8aFH1.season_2013.roundID_9420.teamID_2135.html Domantas Sabonis FIBAEurope.com]</ref> and was tournament leader in rebounds per game.<ref>[http://u18men.fibaeurope.com/en/default.asp?cid={0A5D217A-4698-4FA8-B126-60BCC13F0FEC}&pageID={B23C862E-3DEA-4074-80AD-DC9ECF5AA970}&compID={2248A846-FA78-40FF-B03C-54B460890F45}&season=2013&statCat=RT Players - Statistical Leaders (Rebounds) | U18 EUROPEAN CHAMPIONSHIP MEN - DIVISION A]</ref> His best game was against [[Serbia national basketball team|Serbia]] when he scored 22 points, grabbed 22 rebounds and dished out 3 assists. Lithuania won the game 74-70 in [[Overtime (sports)#Basketball|OT]].<ref>[http://www.basketnews.lt/news-63814-sabonio-vedami-lietuviai-po-pratesimo-parklupde-serbus-statistika.html Sabonio vedami lietuviai po prat\u0119simo parklupd\u0117 serbus (statistika)]</ref> In 2014, coach [[Jonas Kazlauskas]] included Sabonis into preliminary 24 players list for main [[Lithuania men's national basketball team]].<ref>[http://www.fiba.com/pages/eng/fe/14/wcm/news/p/nid/72845/article.html LTU - Numerous options as Kazlauskas announces list for Spain 2014]</ref> In 2014, D.Sabonis played in the [[2014 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship|FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship]] for the second time. This time he averaged 15.9 points, 12.0 rebounds and 3.6 assists per game.<ref>[http://u18men.fibaeurope.com/en/cid_2bqXUaQOJwYn9c2ymJyFx0.teamID_2135.compID_8aYeHlfuGF-mF5IqO8aFH1.season_2014.roundID_10067.playerID_84314.html Domantas Sabonis | U18 EUROPEAN CHAMPIONSHIP MEN - DIVISION A]</ref> He was once again one of the best tournament rebounders, this time outperformed only by Yankuba Sima, who had 12.1 rebounds per game.<ref>[http://u18men.fibaeurope.com/en/default.asp?cid={0A5D217A-4698-4FA8-B126-60BCC13F0FEC}&pageID={B23C862E-3DEA-4074-80AD-DC9ECF5AA970}&compID={2248A846-FA78-40FF-B03C-54B460890F45}&season=2014&statCat=RT Domantas Sabonis |U18 EUROPEAN CHAMPIONSHIP MEN - DIVISION A]</ref> In 2015, Sabonis was once again included into the Lithuania men's national team extended candidates list.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pavie\u0161intas Lietuvos rinktin\u0117s kandidat\u0173 s\u0105ra\u0161as|url=http://www.delfi.lt/sportas/krepsinis/paviesintas-lietuvos-rinktines-kandidatu-sarasas.d?id=67883256|website=Delfi.lt|accessdate=May 5, 2015}}</ref> On July 9, 2015, he was invited to join the Lithuania men's national team training camp for the first time.<ref>{{cite web|title=J. Kazlausko sprendimas: paai\u0161k\u0117jo, kurie krep\u0161ininkai ruo\u0161is Europos \u010dempionatui|url=http://www.delfi.lt/sportas/krepsinis/j-kazlausko-sprendimas-paaiskejo-kurie-krepsininkai-ruosis-europos-cempionatui.d?id=68440712|website=Delfi.lt|accessdate=July 9, 2015}}</ref> On July 15, by participating in [[2015 FIBA Europe Under-20 Championship]], Sabonis achieved the youth tournaments rebounds record by grabbing 28 of them, by doing so he also led Lithuanians to victory versus [[Ukraine national basketball team|Ukraine]] 70\u201357.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sabonis pagerino Europos jaunimo \u010dempionat\u0173 rekord\u0105|url=http://www.basketnews.lt/news-87302-sabonis-pagerino-europos-jaunimo-cempionatu-rekorda.html|website=BasketNews.lt|accessdate=July 15, 2015}}</ref> Not surprisingly, he was the best tournament rebounder as in almost all previous youth competitions, with 13.2 per game this time.<ref>{{cite web|title=Players - Statistical Leaders / U20 Europe Championship Men - Division A|url=http://u20men.fibaeurope.com/en/pageID_pYajECHFHyYitKHgReBji3.compID_UIfgjyQcGqk-fPlnl66Tj0.season_2015.roundID_11585.html|website=u20men.fibaeurope.com|accessdate=July 30, 2015}}</ref> On July 29, Sabonis debuted in Lithuania men's national team during game versus [[Australia men's national basketball team|Australia]] by scoring 4 points and grabbing 7 rebounds.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kazlauskas: \"Domantui dar viskas prie\u0161 akis\" (video)|url=http://www.basketnews.lt/news-87691-kazlauskas-domantui-dar-viskas-pries-akis-video.html|website=BasketNews.lt|accessdate=July 29, 2015}}</ref> By doing so, he immediately became the all-time youngest Lithuanian to debut in a game representing the primary men's national team. Previously, the record was held by the Lithuanian basketball star [[Jonas Valan\u010di\u016bnas]], who did that when he was 19 years and 3 months old. Sabonis performed it being 19 years, 2 months and 26 days old.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Urbonas|first1=Donatas|title=Domant\u0105 Sabon\u012f nuo istorinio \u012fra\u0161o Lietuvos krep\u0161inyje skyr\u0117 nenumatytos aplinkyb\u0117s|url=http://www.15min.lt/24sek/naujiena/lietuva/domantas-sabonis-jauniausias-visu-laiku-lietuvos-rinktines-debiutantas-875-525349|website=24sek.lt|accessdate=September 2, 2015}}</ref> In total, he averaged 6 points and 5.9 rebounds during the preparation games phase, and was the team's second best rebounder after Jonas Valan\u010di\u016bnas.<ref>{{cite web|title=Lietuvos rinktin\u0117s statistika: naudingiausi, rezultatyviausi ir taikliausi|url=http://www.basketnews.lt/news-88608-lietuvos-rinktines-statistika-naudingiausi-rezultatyviausi-ir-taikliausi.html|website=BasketNews.lt|accessdate=September 1, 2015}}</ref> Following the solid performance at such age, Sabonis qualified into the [[Lithuania men's national basketball team]] and represented it at [[EuroBasket 2015]], and won a silver medal during his debut year.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dvejon\u0117s baig\u0117si \u2013 Jonas Kazlauskas paskelb\u0117 galutin\u012f rinktin\u0117s dvyliktuk\u0105|url=http://www.15min.lt/24sek/naujiena/lietuva/dvejones-baigesi-jonas-kazlauskas-paskelbe-galutini-rinktines-dvyliktuka-875-524785|website=24sek.lt|accessdate=September 1, 2015}}</ref> He also was a member of the [[Lithuania national basketball team at 2016 Olympic Games|Lithuanian Olympic national team]] during the [[Basketball at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|2016 Summer Olympics]], where he averaged 5.5 points and 4.5 rebounds.<ref>{{cite web|title=Domantas SABONIS at the Players of the Rio 2016 - Olympic Basketball Tournament (Men) 2016 - FIBA.com|url=http://www.fiba.com/olympics/2016/Domantas-SABONIS|website=FIBA.com|accessdate=November 25, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{NBA player statistics legend}}\n\n===NBA===\n====Regular season====\n{{NBA player statistics start}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{nbay|2016}}\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[2016\u201317 Oklahoma City Thunder season|Oklahoma City]]\n| '''81''' || '''66''' || 20.1 || .399 || .321 || .657 || 3.6 || 1.0 || .5 || '''.4''' || 5.9\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{nbay|2017}}\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[2017\u201318 Indiana Pacers season|Indiana]]\n| 74 || 19 || 24.5 || .514 || .351 || '''.750''' || 7.7 || 2.0 || .5 || '''.4''' || 11.6\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{nbay|2018}}\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[2018\u201319 Indiana Pacers season|Indiana]]\n| 74 || 5 || '''24.8''' || '''.590''' || '''.529''' || .715 || '''9.3''' || '''2.9''' || '''.6''' || '''.4''' || '''14.1'''\n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" colspan=\"2\"|Career\n| 229 || 90 || 23.1 || .513 || .343 || .722 || 6.8 || 1.9 || .6 || .4 || 10.4\n{{s-end}}\n\n====Playoffs====\n{{NBA player statistics start}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[2017 NBA playoffs|2017]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[2016\u201317 Oklahoma City Thunder season|Oklahoma City]]\n| 2 || 0 || 3.0 || .000 || .000 || '''1.000''' || 1.0 || .0 || .5 || '''.5''' || 2.0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[2018 NBA playoffs|2018]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[2017\u201318 Indiana Pacers season|Indiana]]\n| '''7''' |